---
description: Git workflow rules
alwaysApply: true
---

# Git Standards

Every logical task should produce ONE logical commit.

Never mix unrelated work.

---

# Conventional Commits

Use:

feat(scope):
fix(scope):
refactor(scope):
docs(scope):
test(scope):
perf(scope):
style(scope):
ci(scope):
build(scope):
chore(scope):
revert(scope):

---

# Commit Message

Format

type(scope): short summary

Example

feat(authentication): implement refresh tokens

---

# Commit Checklist

Before suggesting a commit verify:

✓ Code complete

✓ No TODOs

✓ No debug code

✓ No commented code

✓ Formatting complete

✓ Lint passes

✓ Tests present for touched behavioral layers (see `.cursor/rules/testing.mdc`)

✓ Relevant `pnpm --filter … test` run and green (do not claim pass without running)

---

# Output

Always finish with:

## Git Commit

Commit:

feat(auth): implement JWT login

Files Modified:

-

Summary:

-

Testing:

-

Breaking Changes:

Yes/No

Migration Required:

Yes/No

---

# Pull Requests

Summarize:

Purpose

Changes

Testing

Risks

Rollback considerations

---

# Atomic Changes

One feature

One bug

One refactor

One commit

Never bundle unrelated work.